---
import Button from '../ui/Button.astro';
import CommandSnippet from '../ui/CommandSnippet.astro';
---

<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="section-shell py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-4xl">
      <div class="mb-4 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-text-muted">
        The OntoSkills directory
      </div>

      <h1 class="max-w-4xl text-5xl font-semibold leading-[0.98] tracking-[-0.05em] text-text-primary sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl">
        Install skills, enable them locally, and query them through MCP.
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-8 text-text-secondary">
        OntoSkills is a minimal product surface for deterministic agent skills: one CLI, one local runtime, one
        official registry, one optional compiler when you need custom source skills.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-8 max-w-3xl">
        <CommandSnippet command="npx ontoskills install mcp" label="Try it now" />
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row">
        <Button href="/getting-started/" size="lg">
          Install now
        </Button>
        <Button href="/explore/" variant="secondary" size="lg">
          Browse skills
        </Button>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 border-t border-white/10 pt-6 sm:grid-cols-3">
        <div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-text-muted">CLI</div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-text-secondary">`ontoskills` installs components, pulls registry skills, and manages local state.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-text-muted">Runtime</div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-text-secondary">`ontomcp` exposes enabled ontologies through a compact, package-aware tool surface.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-text-muted">Compiler</div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-text-secondary">`ontocore` remains optional for teams that author or import raw `SKILL.md` sources.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
